class Solution:
    def getResults(self, queries: List[List[int]]) -> List[bool]:
        w = [[0, 0]]
        r = []
        for q in queries:
            i = 0
            j = len(w) - 1
            while i < j:
                k = math.ceil((i+j)/2)
                if w[k][0] >= q[1]:
                    j = k - 1
                else:
                    i = k
            match q[0]:
                case 1:
                    w.insert(i + 1, [q[1], 0])
                    w[i+1][1] = max(w[i][1], w[i+1][0] - w[i][0])
                    i += 1
                    if i + 1 < len(w):
                        w[i+1][1] = max(w[i][1], w[i+1][0] - w[i][0])
                        i += 1
                    while i+1 < len(w) and w[i][1] < w[i+1][1] and w[i+1][0] - w[i][0] < w[i+1][1]:
                        w[i+1][1] = max(w[i][1], w[i+1][0] - w[i][0])
                        i += 1
                    #print(w, q[1])
                case 2:
                    #print(w, i, q)
                    d = max(q[1] - w[i][0], w[i][1])
                    r.append(d >= q[2])
            """if len(r) == 12:
                break"""
        #print(w)
        return r
